components.cell

Class Cell<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • components.cell.Cell<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the value stored in the cell 
     
 Cell<Integer> intCell = new Cell<>(123);
 Cell<String> strCell = new Cell<>("Hello, World!");
 
 

    public class Cell<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    The Cell class represents a cell with a specific type and value. It uses various type checkers to determine the type of the value assigned to the cell.

    The cell type is determined based on the value provided during the cell creation or when the value is set. The available cell types are managed by a map of CellType to TypeChecker2.
